example-name: Smart tiddler actions
example-description: Action mode with read-only tools — LLM can explore the wiki before responding
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Smart tiddler actions

Action mode with tools enabled. The `tools` filter excludes write tools — only read-only tools are available. The `minimal` context template sends just the title and tags; the LLM uses tools to fetch what it needs.

''Settings covered:'' action mode with tools, `output-mode: text`, `output-target: field:llm-actions-log`, tiddler field precedence

!!! Setup

Add this field to any tiddler:

|!Field |!Value |
|`llm-context-template` |`$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/context-templates/minimal` |

The resolver picks it up via tiddler field precedence (highest priority).

```
<$button>
  Analyze & suggest
  <$llm-action
    tiddler=<<currentTiddler>>
    prompt="Read this tiddler and any related tiddlers. Suggest 3 improvements."
    tools="[tag[$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool]!match[$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/tools/delete-tiddler]!match[$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/tools/set-field]!match[$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/tools/create-tiddler]]"
  />
</$button>
```

!!! Live demo

<$button>
  Analyze & suggest
  <$llm-action
    tiddler=<<currentTiddler>>
    prompt="Read this tiddler and any related tiddlers you find relevant. Then suggest 3 concrete improvements: better title, missing links, or structural changes. Be specific."
    contextTemplate="$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/context-templates/minimal"
    outputTarget="field:llm-actions-log"
    tools="[tag[$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool]!match[$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/tools/delete-tiddler]!match[$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/tools/set-field]!match[$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/tools/create-tiddler]]"
  />
</$button>

<$list filter="[all[current]has[llm-actions-log]]">
''Analysis:''
<div class="rr-settings-info-card">
<$transclude field="llm-actions-log" mode="block"/>
</div>
</$list>
